Students clutch resumes inside branded folders as interview sign-up sheets fill with names, and a whiteboard displays employers scheduling same-day interviews. The engineering society sponsors a resume review table near the stage, while alumni panelists discuss preparing for technical interviews, and alumni volunteers provide quick pep talks near the coffee station. Some students rehearse elevator pitches quietly against the wall, and music enhances the lively atmosphere. Volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures. A post-event survey link flashes on monitors by the exit, as camera crews capture interviews throughout the event, and friends decompress on the quad, discussing company responses.

Inside, a data science company showcased a live dashboard of fair attendance with a post-event survey link on monitors near the exit, and workshops on networking etiquette were conducted in an adjoining classroom. An alumni panel offered insights on preparing for technical interviews, and friends compared which companies showed enthusiasm, marking target employers on the event map. As the day wound down, students exited carrying tote bags filled with business cards, branded notebooks, pens, water bottles, and phone chargers. Volunteers stacked collapsed booths and gathered leftover brochures while announcement chimes signaled the final hour of the fair, with university media capturing interviews throughout the event. An aroma of coffee and catered snacks spread from the lounge.

Workshops are held in an adjoining classroom, and an engineering society-sponsored resume review table is also present. As the event nears its close, volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures following an announcement, marking a smooth conclusion to the bustling scene.
